      "parts": [
        {
          "label": "a",
          "body": "Find the value of $\\log_2 32$.",
          "marks": 2,
          "markscheme": [
            {
              "mark": "M1",
              "note": "write $32 = 2^5$"
            },
            {
              "mark": "A1",
              "note": "$\\log_2 32 = 5$"
            }
          ],
          "answer": "$5$",
          "solution": "$$32 = 2^5 \\Rightarrow \\log_2 32 = 5$$",
          "verify": [
            "Eq(log(32, 2), 5)"
          ]
        },
        {
          "label": "b",
          "body": "Solve $\\log_2 x + \\log_2 (x - 2) = 3$.",
          "marks": 4,
          "markscheme": [
            {
              "mark": "M1",
              "note": "combine: $\\log_2 \\big(x(x - 2)\\big) = 3$"
            },
            {
              "mark": "A1",
              "note": "$x(x - 2) = 8$"
            },
            {
              "mark": "A1",
              "note": "$x = 4$ or $x = -2$ from the quadratic"
            },
            {
              "mark": "R1",
              "note": "reject $x = -2$ (logarithms need $x > 2$); $x = 4$"
            }
          ],
          "answer": "$x = 4$",
          "solution": "**Plan:** combine the logs, convert to index form.$$\\log_2\\big(x(x-2)\\big) = 3 \\Rightarrow x^2 - 2x - 8 = 0 \\Rightarrow (x - 4)(x + 2) = 0$$Both arguments must be positive, so $x = -2$ is rejected and $x = 4$.",
          "verify": [
            "Eq(expand((x - 4)*(x + 2)), x**2 - 2*x - 8)",
            "Eq(4*(4 - 2), 8)"
          ]
        },
        {
          "label": "c",
          "body": "Given that $\\log_2 y = p$, express $\\log_2 \\dfrac{8}{y}$ in terms of $p$.",
          "marks": 2,
          "markscheme": [
            {
              "mark": "M1",
              "note": "split: $\\log_2 8 - \\log_2 y$"
            },
            {
              "mark": "A1",
              "note": "$3 - p$"
            }
          ],
          "answer": "$3 - p$",
          "solution": "$$\\log_2 \\frac{8}{y} = \\log_2 8 - \\log_2 y = 3 - p$$",
          "verify": [
            "Eq(log(8, 2), 3)"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
